In[10]:
def clean_troponin(value):
    if isinstance(value, str) and value.startswith('<'):
        return float(value.replace('<', '').strip())
    try:
        return float(value)
    except:
        return None

df['troponin'] = df['troponin'].apply(clean_troponin)

In[20]:
# ---  LIVER ENZYMES (Gender-Aware & Fixed) ---
print("\n=== LIVER ENZYMES ABNORMALITY ===")
liver_vars = ['alt', 'ast', 'alp', 't_bilirubin', 'albumin']

for var in liver_vars:
    if var == 'albumin':
        # Albumin has low and high cutoffs
        abnormal_low = (df[var] < cutoffs['albumin_low']).sum()
        abnormal_high = (df[var] > cutoffs['albumin_high']).sum()
        total_abnormal = abnormal_low + abnormal_high
        percent_abnormal = total_abnormal / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal "
              f"(Low: {abnormal_low}, High: {abnormal_high})")
    elif var == 't_bilirubin':
        # T_Bilirubin has low and high cutoffs
        abnormal_low = (df[var] < cutoffs['t_bilirubin_low']).sum()
        abnormal_high = (df[var] > cutoffs['t_bilirubin_high']).sum()
        total_abnormal = abnormal_low + abnormal_high
        percent_abnormal = total_abnormal / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal "
              f"(Low: {abnormal_low}, High: {abnormal_high})")
    elif var == 'alp':
        # Gender-specific cutoff for ALP
        abnormal = df.apply(
            lambda row: row[var] > cutoffs['alp_male'] if row['gender'].strip().lower() == 'male' 
                        else row[var] > cutoffs['alp_female'], axis=1)
        percent_abnormal = abnormal.sum() / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal (gender-specific)")
    else:
        # Simple upper cutoff for ALT, AST
        abnormal = (df[var] > cutoffs[var])
        percent_abnormal = abnormal.sum() / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal")

ALBUMIN: 28.2% abnormal (Low: 76, High: 65)

# ---  CARDIAC MARKERS ---
print("\n=== CARDIAC MARKERS ABNORMALITY ===")
cardiac_vars = ['troponin', 'crp', 't_choles', 'ldl', 'hdl', 'tg']

for var in cardiac_vars:
    if var == 'hdl':
        # HDL abnormal if too low
        abnormal = (df[var] < cutoffs['hdl'])
        percent_abnormal = abnormal.sum() / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal (< {cutoffs['hdl']})")
    else:
        # Others abnormal if too high
        abnormal = (df[var] > cutoffs[var])
        percent_abnormal = abnormal.sum() / len(df) * 100
        print(f"{var.upper()}: {percent_abnormal:.1f}% abnormal (> {cutoffs[var]})")

# RBS abnormal if > 7.8 mmol/L

print(f"RBS: {percent_abnormal_rbs:.1f}% abnormal (> {cutoffs['rbs']} mmol/L)")

# HBA1C categories
hba1c_normal = (df['hba1c'] < cutoffs['hba1c_normal']).sum()
hba1c_prediabetes = ((df['hba1c'] >= cutoffs['hba1c_normal']) & (df['hba1c'] <= cutoffs['hba1c_prediabetes'])).sum()
hba1c_diabetes = (df['hba1c'] >= cutoffs['hba1c_diabetes']).sum()

print(f"HBA1C Normal (<{cutoffs['hba1c_normal']}%): {hba1c_normal} patients")
print(f"HBA1C Pre-Diabetes ({cutoffs['hba1c_normal']}{cutoffs['hba1c_prediabetes']}%): {hba1c_prediabetes} patients")
print(f"HBA1C Diabetes ({cutoffs['hba1c_diabetes']}%): {hba1c_diabetes} patients")

In[40]:
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind, mannwhitneyu, shapiro

#  Variables to test
liver_vars = ['alt', 'ast', 'alp', 't_bilirubin', 'albumin']
cardiac_vars = ['crp', 'ldl', 'hdl', 'tg']
test_vars = liver_vars + cardiac_vars

print(" Step 4.1: Comparing Continuous Variables Between CVD Groups")
print(" Testing if liver & cardiac markers differ between CVD Negative (0) and CVD Positive (1) patients.\n")

step4_1_results = []

for var in test_vars:
    group0 = df[df['cvd_status'] == 0][var]
    group1 = df[df['cvd_status'] == 1][var]

    #  Mean  SD for each group
    mean0, std0 = group0.mean(), group0.std()
    mean1, std1 = group1.mean(), group1.std()
    mean_sd_group0 = f"{mean0:.2f}  {std0:.2f}"
    mean_sd_group1 = f"{mean1:.2f}  {std1:.2f}"

    #  Normality check
    stat0, p0 = shapiro(group0)
    stat1, p1 = shapiro(group1)
    normal0 = p0 > 0.05
    normal1 = p1 > 0.05

    #  Choose test
    if normal0 and normal1:
        stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group0, group1, equal_var=False)
        test_used = 't-test'
    else:
        stat, p_value = mannwhitneyu(group0, group1, alternative='two-sided')
        test_used = 'Mann-Whitney U'

    step4_1_results.append({
        'Variable': var.upper(),
        'Group 0 (CVD Negative)': mean_sd_group0,
        'Group 1 (CVD Positive)': mean_sd_group1,
        'Test Used': test_used,
        'P-Value': round(p_value, 4),
        'Normality (CVD Negative)': normal0,
        'Normality (CVD Positive)': normal1
    })

#  Convert to DataFrame
import pandas as pd
step4_1_df = pd.DataFrame(step4_1_results)

#  Display results
print("Step 4.1 Results: Continuous Variables (CVD Groups)")
display(step4_1_df)
